article.headline: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 95, Texas-Arlington 83
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Justin Reynolds had 26 points and 10 rebounds as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi defeated Texas-Arlington 95-83 on Wednesday night, ending an eight-game losing streak. Garland Judkins and Demond Watt each had 14 points and Antonio Topps added 12 points. Terence Jones had 10 points and 10 assists for the Islanders (9-21, 4-11 Southland). LaMarcus Reed led all scorers with 27 points for Texas-Arlington (13-15, 7-8). Cameron Catlett scored 13 points, Bo Ingram scored 11 and Jordan Reves had 10 points for the Mavericks. The Islanders' last win came on Jan. 29 at Stephen F. Austin. They went 0-8 in February.
